channel.title: I Need Help Getting My RSPS Public
channel.description: I have a no-ip account set up and I have allowed port 43594 through windows firewall and also set it up to be used in Utorrent under connection settings. I also have the no-ip client enabled with my server check box checked. I have portforwarded my router settings for a TCP/UDP port on my static IP address 192.168.1.10. I have also configured client.java and gui.java in my server client to my no-ip address. I have tested it with PFPortchecker and it says my port is not open or reachable. Can someone please help me i have looked into many tutorials on here today and followed all the steps.

item.title: I Need Help Getting My RSPS Public
item.dc:creator: @ITI_Basak_ITI ITI Basak ITI
item.description:
@ITI_Basak_ITI wrote:

First off, If you have your router set up to portforward, using uTorrent will only for kinda of a double negative effect. 2 Programs trying to do the same thing messes things up. If you have your router portforwarding 43594, uTorrent isnt needed at all and you should get rid of it. uTorrent should only be used as a last resort. One thing, when you close uTorrent, it still runs on your computer. You need to go to the files search in the start menu, Type task Manager, find the uTorrent process, and end it. Once you have uTorrent disabledm and Router correctly port forwarding 43594, try the pfPort checker. Run it with no other windows open. Hopefullly this helps
